            <thetext>The Simulator component requires a number of settings, e.g. the Selenium server&#39;s host name and port number or the AUT&#39;s URL. Currently, these are defined as config settings in the simulation-build. This means that the Simulator application must be rebuilt every time these settings are changed, which is very inconvenient. Run-time settings should instead be moved to the simulation-run job. The Generator should append these settings to the shell command that launches the Simulator in Rhino. simulator.unit.TestLoader could then read these options and turn them into qx settings.</thetext>
